{
  "stem": "26765.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the idea of death and what comes after death is pictured in my mind as if we're going to dance into heaven, and there will be a beautiful ballroom-- because of this song my mother sang.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember many other songs she taught me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Do you know the names of any of it-- of the other ones?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She sang another song that was a hit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's why I-- I think my mother, you know, taught them to me rather than at a nursery school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Another song was a carnival hit, 'Heidewitzka, Herr Kapitaen', and some children songs, 'War Ein Sein Kleines,' 'Bin Allein Zum, Zum, Zum, Zum', and other children's songs she taught me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That I'm not sure about.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What my aunt told me was that my mother's side of the family was much more liberal-- not religious at all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father's side of the family was more religious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember eating matzah.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- I've always loved to eat matzah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think it stems from the fact that we ate it at home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember we ate matzah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I don't really remember the religious services.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not consciously.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Consciously, I didn't, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I-- I never thought to myself, well, I am Jewish, or that I had any reason to believe I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I know we ate matzah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That that's about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after Kristallnacht, my mother, of course, was desperate for her two children-- my brother George, who is five years older than I, and myself.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she contacted my uncle Joseph, who was here in America, who was married to my mother's sister.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she wrote them and told them what had happened to both my father and my uncle Ludwig.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
